    <p>A number of popular base themes provide many useful tools to help in front-end development. These range from simple things such as disabling the theme registry that allieviates the need to clear cache when adding new templates, functions etc, to giving you complete control over how and where your CSS and JavaScript are added to the page.</p>

<p>The <a href="https://drupal.org/project/magic">Magic Module</a> consolidates a number of these useful tools into one place.</p>
